CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 9, 1967, pg. 15, reads: "ULG Boat Ride - For the past few years, one of the social highlights of the season has been a boat ride sponsored by the Urban League Guild of Pittsburgh. This year was no exception and a happy throng was on hand for the event held recently.  Among Guild members who spearheaded the affair were those in first picture.  From left they are: Mmes. Arlene Palamore, Margaretta Burton, Helen Chalfont, chairman; Mary Alexander, president, and Juanita McCarter...- All Harris photos."
TitMainTitle: Men and women, including Vernita Golden Winston and Gloria Golden Grate near center, gathered in front of stack of life jackets, on riverboat for Urban League Guild of Pittsburgh's annual boat ride
